\pard\f0\fs28  Plants from the Iberian peninsula have been treated as subsp.{\b  patula} (Desf.) Maire in Jahandiez & Maire, {\i Cat. Pl. Maroc}{\b  3}: 642 (1934). They have the leaves usually cordate at the base (rarely rounded), and the calyx more zygomorphic. Similar plants occur elsewhere in the range, and they are not worth subspecific rank.
