\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 17. S. candidissima} Vahl,{\i  Enum. Pl.}{\b  1}: 278 (1804). Perennial up to 60 cm. Stems simple or little-branched, glandular above. Leaves simple, petiolate, ovate, cordate at base, acute, pannose. Verticillasters with 2-6 flowers. Bracts less than 1/3 as long as calyx, green; pedicels c. 2 mm. Calyx c. 10 mm, densely glandular-pubescent. Corolla 20-30 mm, white with a few purple spots on lower palate; upper lip strongly falcate.{\i  S. Albania, W. Greece.} Al Gr. ({\i S.W. Asia}.)
